Anthony Weiner, a former congressman who resigned in 2011 over a sexting scandal found himself leading a 2013 poll of candidates running for New York City mayor.
After losing in the Democratic primary, Weiner in 2017 pleaded guilty to sexting with a minor and served two years in prison before his release last year.
Eliot Spitzer is another example of a politician unable to recover from his scandal.
The once-popular governor has never recovered from that scandal and even lost the race for New York City Comptroller in 2013.
